Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Production date: 213 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 134, 4. Name Charmokles. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 273.40.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0660)
